

Copy


Sir
Salisbury 31st: October 1777



By perusing the inclosed copy you will be able to judge what further measures will be necessary, for you to take to expedite the liberation of yourself by accomplishing the wishd for exchange, which I hope will now soon take place.
As I am fearful of missing the present opportunity of forwarding this I cannot add more than that I am with great respect Sir your humble Servant,

(Signed) Heman Allen
Colol: Archd: Campbell

